        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-05 06:06:59.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOne question. Does that change imply that CBA file has to both have \"CBA\" string in it's name as well as be defined to be of type \"CONTROLLER_BLUEPRINT_ARCHIVE\", or only the substring is checked? If the latter option apply, shouldn't we check both?",
