      },
      {
        "id": "3537f865244efd49f302a7019a3d5917faf31918",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5040,
          "name": "Dmitrii Puzikov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "d.puzikov2@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "dpuzikov"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-03-05 08:33:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> One question. Does that change imply that CBA file has to both have \"CBA\" string in it's name as well as be defined to be of type \"CONTROLLER_BLUEPRINT_ARCHIVE\", or only the substring is checked? If the latter option apply, shouldn't we check both?\n\nCurrently only file name is checked. From my point of view we should rely not on the file name but on the manifest type entry.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
